This is Perl module Apporo.

INSTALLATION

Perl module Apporo is Perl binding for Apporo (http://code.google.com/p/apporo/)

Apporo installation isn't straightforward.

You should install tsubomi before installing apporo.
And you should install apporo before installing the Perl module Apporo.

    % cd YOUR_TMP_DIR
    % svn checkout http://tsubomi.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/ tsubomi
    % cd tsubomi/src/tsubomi
    % make
    % sudo make install
    % cd ../../../
    % svn checkout http://apporo.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/ apporo
    % cd apporo/src
    % make
    % sudo make install
    % cd ../../

After these, if your CPAN shell is set up,you should just be able to do

    % cpan Apporo

Download it, unpack it, then build it as per the usual:

    % perl Makefile.PL
    % make && make test

Then install it:

    % make install

DOCUMENTATION

Apporo documentation is available as in POD. So you can do:

    % perldoc Apporo

to read the documentation online with your favorite pager.

Toshinori Satou (@overlast)
